Why add media/?

Version 1 revolves around downloadable academic materials (PDFs, documents, etc.). Django stores uploaded files using MEDIA_ROOT, so creating this directory from the start keeps file handling organized.

Why add static/?

Even though the React frontend will eventually serve most static assets, Django still uses static files for the admin interface and any backend-managed assets. Keeping a dedicated static/ directory follows Django conventions and simplifies production configuration later.

