Architectural Decision: python-decouple vs django-environ

There are two common choices for managing environment variables.

Option 1: python-decouple

Pros

Very simple to learn.
Great for small and medium projects.
Minimal configuration.

Cons

Less feature-rich than django-environ.
Option 2: django-environ

Pros

More powerful.
Excellent for complex deployments.
Supports advanced environment parsing.

Cons

Slightly steeper learning curve.
Recommendation for FutMxStore V1

I recommend python-decouple.

Why?

Faster to set up.
Easy to understand.
Meets all our current requirements.
Easy to replace later if the project grows.

This is another example of Architect for the Future. Implement for the Present.

